item.title: How Sparse Can We Prune A Deep Network: A Geometric Viewpoint

item.title: Path Neural Networks: Expressive and Accurate Graph Neural Networks
item.description: We derive three different variants of the PathNN model that aggregate single shortest paths, all shortest paths and all simple paths of length up to K. We prove that two of these variants are strictly more powerful than the 1-WL algorithm, and we experimentally validate our theoretical results.
